d PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527257\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527257\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 09, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104epv1665703147858.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/epv1665703147858.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/epv1665703147858.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"epv1665703147858\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Returns the outermost DOM node attached to the field that was in error. If the field in error\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"epv1665703147858__topic_d127154e1_d127155e1_d127156e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"epv1665703147858__p_d127157e1_d127158e1_d127159e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Return</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">FieldErrorContext</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">.</code>\n<span class=\"keyword apiname\">getBoundElement()</span>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"epv1665703147858__section_w1222ab1b5b3_w1223ab1b5_w1224ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d679705e70\">Return Value</h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"epv1665703147858__parml_ixp_2r5_cwb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\">Return</dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Outermost browser DOM node for the field that was in error, for the default View.</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\">Null</dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">If the field is not in the layout and or not in the default view.</dd>\n</dl>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"epv1665703147858__section_w1225ab1b5b5_w1226ab1b5_w1227ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d679705e97\">Exceptions</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following exceptions may be thrown:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">uniface.InvalidDataObjectException</code></li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"epv1665703147858__section_w1228ab1b5b7_w1229ab1b5_w1230ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d679705e114\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"epv1665703147858__p_d127178e1_d127179e1_d127180e1\">The <span class=\"keyword apiname\">getBoundElement()</span> function\n        makes it possible to access the underlying DOM nodes for Uniface fields. Using the returned\n        DOM node, you can find out what the parent or sibling nodes are so that you can, for example\n        apply error classes.</p>\n<div class=\"note important note_important\" id=\"epv1665703147858__note_922d0b9eeed2d1ead768e1bc4b97b091\"><span class=\"note__title\">Important:</span> To make changes to a DOM\n        element that is bound to Uniface objects, use only the Uniface JavaScript data accessing\n        APIs. Do not try to manipulate DOM nodes directly.</div>\n</section>\n<div class=\"example\" id=\"epv1665703147858__example_xgb_nr5_cwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d679705e129\">Changing Error Reporting</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"epv1665703147858__p_d127184e1_d127185e1_d127186e1\">The following example changes the default reporting of\n        server-side validation errors. When the server encounters a validation error, it returns a\n        response with the error information, then <code class=\"ph codeph\">webtrigger showError</code> is fired. By\n        default, Uniface sets an error class on the element bound to the field that is in error, and\n        CSS can be used to style it appropriately.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"epv1665703147858__p_d127187e1_d127188e1_d127189e1\">The following code overwrites the default behavior and\n        sets the error class to the parent element of the element bound to the field:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104epv1665703147858_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"epv1665703147858__codeblock_uqb_pr5_cwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">webtrigger showError\n javascript \n // Get bound element of field in error\n var fieldElement = this.getBoundElement();\n // Get parent of element\n var parentEl = fieldEl.parentElement;\n // Set error class on parent element instead of the field element itself\n parentEl.classList.add(\"-highlight-error-\");\n // Prevent default error reporting\n return false;\n endjavascript\nend</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527257\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527257\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "getBoundElement() Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 09, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Returns the outermost DOM node attached to the field that was in error. If the field in error Return = FieldErrorContext . getBoundElement() Return Value Return Outermost browser DOM node for the field that was in error, for the default View. Null If the field is not in the layout and or not in the default view. Exceptions The following exceptions may be thrown: uniface.InvalidDataObjectException Description The getBoundElement() function makes it possible to access the underlying DOM nodes for Uniface fields. Using the returned DOM node, you can find out what the parent or sibling nodes are so that you can, for example apply error classes. Important: To make changes to a DOM element that is bound to Uniface objects, use only the Uniface JavaScript data accessing APIs. Do not try to manipulate DOM nodes directly. Changing Error Reporting The following example changes the default reporting of server-side validation errors. When the server encounters a validation error, it returns a response with the error information, then webtrigger showError is fired. By default, Uniface sets an error class on the element bound to the field that is in error, and CSS can be used to style it appropriately. The following code overwrites the default behavior and sets the error class to the parent element of the element bound to the field: Explain this code webtrigger showError javascript // Get bound element of field in error var fieldElement = this.getBoundElement(); // Get parent of element var parentEl = fieldEl.parentElement; // Set error class on parent element instead of the field element itself parentEl.classList.add(\"-highlight-error-\"); // Prevent default error reporting return false; endjavascript end Copy Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}